rm — remove files and directories

SYNOPSIS
  rm [-r] [-f] PATH...

DESCRIPTION
  Removes each PATH. Refuses to remove "/" outright. With -r (recursive)
  walks into directories before removing them; with -f (force) missing
  operands are ignored and write errors do not change the exit status.

  OCOS's vfs has no atomic rmdir-on-empty: -r reads each directory,
  removes children one by one, and only then removes the directory.

EXAMPLES
  rm tmpfile
  rm -r build/
  rm -rf /tmp/work               idempotent cleanup

SEE ALSO
  mkdir(1), cp(1), mv(1), find(1)
